\begin_layout Section
Pairwise available case estimator
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The available case estimator is a popular estimator of kappa coefficients with missing data.
 It is the default estimator in the R package irrCAC when the data contains missing values.
 If we let 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{i}^{\star}$
\end_inset

 be the complete observations and 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{ij}$
\end_inset

 the missingness indicators for the 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

th rater,
 we may define the available case Conger's kappa estimator as 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\kappa}_{C}^{AC}=1-\hat{d}^{AC}/\hat{d}_{C}^{AC}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\hat{d}^{AC} & = & \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}\sum_{j<k}l(X_{ij}^{\star},X_{ik}^{\star})M_{ij}M_{ik}}{\sum_{i=1}^{n}\sum_{j<k}M_{ij}M_{ik}},\quad\hat{d}_{C}^{AC}=\frac{\sum_{i,i'}\sum_{j<k}l(X_{ij}^{\star},X_{i'k}^{\star})M_{ij}M_{i'k}}{\sum_{i,i'}\sum_{j<k}M_{ij}M_{i'k}}.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

The available case estimators of Fleiss' kappa and the Brennan–Prediger coefficient are defined in the same way.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The estimator has been studied,
